Title: Object: Geometrical elevations of the west fronts of the Cathedrals of Salisbury, Norwich, St Paul's London, St Peter's Rome, and the Great Pyramid of Egypt, to one scale
Description: Elevation of the different buildings, placed in front of each other to show the relative sizes of each, the pyramid at the back. 1831 Etching and aquatint
Producer name: Print made by: Robert Havell I
Print made by: Thomas Hutchings Clarke
Bibliographic references: Crace 1878 / A Catalogue of Maps, Plans and Views of London, Westminster and Southwark, collected and arranged by Frederick Crace (XIX.174)
